A horrific crash on the M7 Edwin Swales and Titren Road intersection claimed the life of a nine-year-old boy, on Monday.Rescue Care paramedics arrived on the scene to find carnage. Spokesperson for Rescue Care, Garrith Jamieson, said that a truck had T-boned a vehicle at the intersection. “The vehicle which had a father and his two children in it was significantly damaged. Paramedics found a little boy on the side of the road with critical injuries. As they worked on the boy, he went into cardiac arrest. Immediately, a full resuscitation took place and the child responded well. He was quickly rushed to a nearby hospital for the urgent care that he required. However, a few hours later, due to his injuries, the child passed away,” Jamieson said.He added that the father and the second child were also injured and transported to hospital. “The truck driver sustained minor injuries and was treated on scene and transported to hospital,” said Jamieson. KZN police spokesperson, Captain Nqobile Gwala, said that a case of culpable homicide is being investigated by Bellair SAPS. “It is alleged that on 2 March at 5:15pm, two vehicles were involved in a collision on the M7 Highway and Titren Road intersection. A nine-year-old boy was rushed to hospital after he sustained serious injuries and he later died. The matter is still under investigation,” Gwala said.